I stand before this court today to accept full responsibility for my actions and acknowledge my guilt in accepting a bribe and suppressing the publication of an article. As stated in the case at hand, I am guilty of being bribed, as I accepted a total of 4000 pounds in exchange for not publishing an article that uncovered that this company emits one million tonnes of CO2 more per year than what they claim.

I deeply regret my involvement in this illegal activity and the consequences it has had. I now fully understand the gravity of my actions and the harm they may have caused. It is evident from the events that unfolded that my actions allowed for the continuation of misleading claims, despite my initial belief that it would only have a temporary impact.

I humbly submit myself to the judgment of this court and express my remorse for the harm I have caused. My guilty plea reflects my genuine regret and willingness to accept the consequences for my wrongdoing. I am committed to making amends and rectifying the aftermath of my actions.

I assure the court that I have taken this matter seriously and understand the significant impact it has had. I am prepared to face the appropriate measures deemed necessary to atone for my transgressions.

Thank you for your attention and consideration.

Sincerely,
Jack Palmer
